Thought and Reflection


Watch Night Service
New Years Eve 2010

It was a blessed event. Over 50 strong in attendance. We brought in the New Year with communion, song, prayer and praise. Being in the house of the Lord is always good and on this night the message of the evening was "STAY FOCUSED" because the "BEST IS YET TO COME". We gave thanks for all he has done and all He has in store for 2011, you only need to be saved and believe in your heart. At St. Paul's Baptist Church, change is the order of the day.

Come see!

Honoring Reverend
Myrna E. Graham

On December 12, 2010 St. Paul's Baptist Church honored Reverend Myrna E. Graham during Sunday Service. What a most auspicious event! Thanks to the many friends, family and St. Paul's members in attendance, Rev. Myrna Graham was shown much love and appreciation. The event was followed by dinner and fellowship.
